### Image-to-Image Transformation (Super-Resolution) with Transformers.js

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

This example demonstrates image super-resolution using the image-to-image pipeline in Transformers.js. It takes a low-resolution image URL and upscales it. The output is a RawImage object that can be displayed in a browser or saved to a file in Node.js environments. The required library is '@huggingface/transformers'.

```javascript
import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Super-resolution (upscaling)
const upscaler = await pipeline(
    'image-to-image',
    'Xenova/swin2SR-classical-sr-x2-64'
);

const url = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/lowres.jpg';
const result = await upscaler(url);
console.log(result);
// Output: [RawImage { width: 512, height: 512, channels: 3 }]

// Save or display the upscaled image (browser)
const canvas = document.getElementById('output');
const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
ctx.drawImage(result[0].toCanvas(), 0, 0);

// Save image (Node.js)
import fs from 'fs';
result[0].save('upscaled.png');
```

