### Compute Text Embeddings on WebGPU using Transformers.js

Source: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.js/blob/main/docs/source/guides/webgpu.md

This snippet demonstrates how to use the Transformers.js library to perform text embedding extraction utilizing WebGPU acceleration. It requires the '@huggingface/transformers' package and specifies 'webgpu' as the device for computation.

```javascript
import { pipeline } from "@huggingface/transformers";

// Create a feature-extraction pipeline
const extractor = await pipeline(
  "feature-extraction",
  "mixedbread-ai/mxbai-embed-xsmall-v1",
  { device: "webgpu" },
);

// Compute embeddings
const texts = ["Hello world!", "This is an example sentence."];
const embeddings = await extractor(texts, { pooling: "mean", normalize: true });
console.log(embeddings.tolist());
// [
//   [-0.016986183822155, 0.03228696808218956, -0.0013630966423079371, ... ],
//   [0.09050482511520386, 0.07207386940717697, 0.05762749910354614, ... ],
// ]
```

