### Run Object Detection Inference with Transformers.js

Source: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.js/blob/main/docs/source/tutorials/vanilla-js.md

This JavaScript function `detect` utilizes the `detector` pipeline from Transformers.js to perform object detection on an image source. It sets an analysis status, awaits the model's output, and logs the results. The function supports setting a confidence threshold and returning bounding box coordinates as percentages. It requires the `detector` object to be initialized previously.

```javascript
async function detect(img) {
  status.textContent = "Analysing...";
  const output = await detector(img.src, {
    threshold: 0.5,
    percentage: true,
  });
  status.textContent = "";
  console.log("output", output);
  // ...
}
```
